description: Fill soft tacos with lean beef mince and kaleslaw for a quick-to-assemble midweek meal that’s ready in 15 minutes.
keywords: Tortilla,Seafood free,Tree nut free,Low sugar,Beef,High protein,High fibre,Soy free,Kale,Mince,Quick & easy lunch,Dinner Made Easy,Peanut free
name: Quick Beef & Kaleslaw Tortillas Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 30g sachet Old El Paso Mexican reduced salt mild taco spice mix
193g Old El Paso stand ‘n stuff soft tortillas

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 140°C/120°C fan-forced. Remove tortillas from packaging and wrap in foil. Bake for 8 minutes or until warm.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Add mince and cook, breaking up lumps with a wooden spoon, for 5 minutes or until browned. Add spice mix and 3/4 cup water. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Place kaleslaw, reserving seed mix, in a bowl. Add dressing from kit and toss to combine.
Remove tortillas from foil. Spoon a little kaleslaw mixture into tortillas, then top with mince and seed mixture from kit. Serve with any remaining kaleslaw.
